# Basic Components

Basic components are the fundamental building blocks of the interface. They are designed to be simple, reusable, and composable.

## Text Input
Found in [text-input.css](mdc:components/text-input.css)

```html
<div class="text-input size-medium">
    <div class="label">
        <span class="label-text">Label Text</span>
    </div>
    <div class="content">
        <input type="text" placeholder="Placeholder text">
    </div>
</div>
```

Size variants: `size-small`, `size-medium`, `size-large`, `size-full`
States: `disabled`, `error`, `required`

## Select
Found in [select.css](mdc:components/select.css)

```html
<div class="select">
    <div class="label">
        <span class="label-text">Label Text</span>
    </div>
    <div class="select-wrapper">
        <select class="select-trigger">
            <option value="" disabled selected>Select an option</option>
            <option value="option1">Option 1</option>
        </select>
    </div>
</div>
```

States: `disabled`, `required`

## Buttons
Found in [buttons.css](mdc:components/buttons.css)

```html
<button class="btn btn-primary btn-medium">
    <span class="btn-text">Button Text</span>
</button>
```

Style variants: `btn-primary`, `btn-secondary`
Size variants: `btn-medium`, `btn-small`
Special variants: `btn-icon-only` (requires `btn-icon` inner element)
